OL,3,CWhy is Nigel Farage in trouble over #5
OL,4,Cmillion?
OL,6,FHarborne, a Thai-based cryptocurrency
OL,7,Finvestor, gave Farage #5m in April
OL,8,F2024 - just weeks before Farage
OL,9,Fdecided to stand in the 2024 general
OL,10,Felection and take over as Reform UK
OL,11,Fleader.
OL,13,FThe gift was not reported at the time,
OL,14,Fand was first reported by the Guardian
OL,15,Fat the end of April 2026.
OL,17,FWhat was the #5 million gift used for?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1779329020
OL,3,CWhy is Nigel Farage in trouble over #5
OL,4,Cmillion?
OL,6,FNigel Farage told the Daily Telegraph
OL,7,Fthe money was used to pay for his
OL,8,Fprivate security. He later told
OL,9,Fbroadcasters he had "no obligation" to
OL,10,Fdeclare the gift and that it was
OL,11,F"purely private" and "wasn't political
OL,12,Fin any sense at all".
OL,14,FThe Reform UK leader later told The
OL,15,FSun the money was given as a "reward
OL,16,Ffor campaigning for Brexit".
OL,18,FFarage also said he "cannot be bought
OL,19,Fby anybody" and the money from
OL,20,FChristopher Harborne was given on a
OL,21,F"completely unconditional basis".
OL,26,@qD@UOUqD@cO]
